    "Dynamic Rank Allocation: Iintroduce a lightweight mechanism to adjust LoRA adapter ranks on-the-fly during training.",
    "Instead of fixing ranks across all layers, DRaFT-Q uses gradient-driven signals to expand rank capacity for layers with high learning demand and reduce it for simpler layers.",
    "This mechanism enables efficient and adaptive use of the rank budget throughout training.2.",
    "Reward-Sensitive Fine-Tuning: Ipropose a reward-weighted loss formulation that emphasizes semantically important tokens during supervised fine-tuning.",
    "By upweighting tokens associated with correct answers and reasoning-critical segments, DRaFT-Q accelerates convergence and improves task-specific generalization."
